        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 8 at 4:27PM CDT until July 8 at 5:00PM CDT by NWS Lincoln IL</headline>
        <description>SVRILX

The National Weather Service in Lincoln has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northeastern Christian County in central Illinois...
East central Sangamon County in central Illinois...
Southwestern Macon County in central Illinois...

* Until 500 PM CDT.

* At 427 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Mount Auburn,
or 13 miles north of Taylorville, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* This severe thunderstorm will be near...
Stonington around 440 PM CDT.

Other locations in the path of this severe thunderstorm include Blue
Mound.

This includes Interstate 72 between mile markers 120 and 122.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
